What's going on? You said you
wanted a bed, which you got,

775
00:42:39,083 --> 00:42:41,874
and clean clothes and a shower,
which you also got.

776
00:42:41,875 --> 00:42:46,207
- You look great, actually.
- Stop. I told you, I'm done.

777
00:42:46,208 --> 00:42:47,582
- I need to go home.
- To what?

778
00:42:47,583 --> 00:42:49,416
My life.

779
00:42:49,417 --> 00:42:52,416
You'd trade all this for
a studio apartment in Brooklyn?

780
00:42:52,417 --> 00:42:54,708
Yeah. I don't like being
surrounded

781
00:42:54,709 --> 00:42:56,541
- by gun-toting crazies.
- That's why you gotta stay,

782
00:42:56,542 --> 00:42:59,916
protect me
from the lunatic fringe.

783
00:42:59,917 --> 00:43:02,457
[knock on door]

784
00:43:02,458 --> 00:43:04,708
Uh, Dad says food's ready.

785
00:43:04,709 --> 00:43:09,166
Thanks, J.J.
We'll be right there.

786
00:43:11,667 --> 00:43:15,124
Hey, J.J.! Hold on.

787
00:43:15,125 --> 00:43:18,749
J.J.! You...
you heard us talkin'.

788
00:43:18,750 --> 00:43:21,416
- It's none of my business.
- Oh, it is your business.

789
00:43:21,417 --> 00:43:24,582
I've been on the run
for nearly 60 days,

790
00:43:24,583 --> 00:43:27,249
and the only reason the Feds
haven't caught up with me

791
00:43:27,250 --> 00:43:31,249
is because of the courage and
kindness of families like yours.

792
00:43:31,250 --> 00:43:32,582
I was having trouble in there

793
00:43:32,583 --> 00:43:35,040
with the world's worst
girlfriend,

794
00:43:35,041 --> 00:43:36,958
and I said something
I'm not proud of.

795
00:43:36,959 --> 00:43:39,249
- It's okay.
- It's not okay.

796
00:43:39,250 --> 00:43:43,583
I ask your forgiveness.

797
00:43:47,041 --> 00:43:49,792
Do you...
think we're crazy?

798
00:43:54,083 --> 00:43:56,999
Anyone who stands up
for what they believe,

799
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:58,666
people are gonna say
they're crazy.

800
00:43:58,667 --> 00:44:00,791
They've been calling me that
for years.

801
00:44:00,792 --> 00:44:04,499
But what you and your daddy
have made here

802
00:44:04,500 --> 00:44:08,082
is the very opposite
of crazy.

803
00:44:08,083 --> 00:44:10,374
It's blessed.

804
00:44:10,375 --> 00:44:12,834
I'm proud to be fightin'
on your side.

805
00:44:15,041 --> 00:44:18,583
[both chuckle]

806
00:44:23,083 --> 00:44:28,000
[police radio chatter]

807
00:44:29,875 --> 00:44:32,833
I was speaking
to your colleague.

808
00:44:32,834 --> 00:44:33,958
